<item>
            <title>[LU-12127] Improve LFSCK orphan handling </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12127</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After landing patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/32959/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/32959/&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11111&quot; title=&quot;crash doing LFSCK: orph_index_insert()) ASSERTION( !(obj-&amp;gt;mod_flags &amp;amp; ORPHAN_OBJ)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11111&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11111&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lfsck: skip orphan processing&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to fix the common cause of crashes due to LFSCK processing open-unlinked files, there is still a potential improvement in orphan processing remaining in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/34174&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/34174&lt;/a&gt; to limit the scope of the 32959 patch to namespace scanning rather than layout scanning, in case the open-unlinked file is also corrupted. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch is for tracking the second patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
